# ============================================================================
# 15. MEMORY MANAGEMENT
# ============================================================================

## 15.1 Buffer Allocation
- Pre-allocate buffers where possible
- Use `std::vector::reserve()` for known sizes
- Avoid dynamic allocation in real-time loops
- Use lock-free ring buffers (SPSC) for high-throughput data

## 15.2 Memory Limits
- Pipeline queue size: ~10 MB configurable
- IQ buffer: Match SDR sample rate (e.g., 1024-8192 samples)
- Keep total memory usage under 500 MB per module

## 15.3 Smart Pointers
- Use `std::unique_ptr` for ownership
- Use `std::shared_ptr` only when needed
- **NEVER** use raw pointers for owned resources
- Use `std::weak_ptr` for breaking cycles

# ============================================================================
# 16. PROTOCOL ANALYSIS (Module 4.2)
# ============================================================================

## 16.1 Decision Tree Rules
```
IF modulation == 4FSK AND class == BURST AND bandwidth ~= 12.5 kHz:
    protocol = DMR, multiplexing = TDMA

IF modulation == GMSK AND class == BURST:
    protocol = GSM, multiplexing = TDMA

IF modulation == QPSK AND class == CONTINUOUS AND bandwidth ~= 25 kHz:
    protocol = TETRA, multiplexing = FDMA
```

## 16.2 FHSS Detection
Criteria:
- `hop_count >= 5`
- `power_variance < 3 dB`
- Consistent hop rate
- Signal class = BURST

# ============================================================================
# 17. DATABASE AND PERSISTENCE (Module 4.2)
# ============================================================================

## 17.1 SQLite Schema
```sql
CREATE TABLE signals (
    timestamp INTEGER,
    frequency REAL,
    bandwidth REAL,
    modulation TEXT,
    protocol TEXT,
    rssi_dbm REAL,
    snr_db REAL,
    aoa_degrees REAL,
    target_lat REAL,
    target_lon REAL,
    payload TEXT
);
```

## 17.2 Logging Strategy
- Use **WAL mode** for SQLite (`PRAGMA journal_mode=WAL`)
- **Batch insertions** (100+ records at once)
- **Asynchronous logging** thread
- Support CSV export for analysis

